# Goals

---

## ApiSources-G1 API Source Configuration supports multi-provider LLM management with auto-detection and model tiers
**Status:** proposed
**Tags:** stack:backend
**Depends on:** AgentConfig-G1, Runtime-G3

ApiSource data model supports Anthropic, OpenAI, and Local providers with per-source models. ModelTier enum (Min / Lite / Mid / Pro / Max) tags each model for display grouping. AgentConfig references concrete model IDs (model_id) instead of tiers, enabling direct model selection per agent regardless of how many tiers an ApiSource covers. First-startup auto-detection finds existing Claude keys, OpenAI keys, and Ollama instances. API sources persisted to `dirs::data_local_dir()/autoforge/api_sources.json`. CRUD API endpoints for creating, reading, updating, and deleting API sources. Multi-provider AI dispatch routes chat requests to the correct provider (Anthropic SSE, OpenAI streaming, Local/Ollama). API key resolution priority: env var → ~/.claude/settings.json → stored (base64). Test Connection endpoint verifies API source connectivity and credentials. APIs top-level view with source list, detail editor, and model management table. First-startup UI guides user when no API source is configured.

Currently AutoForge only supports Anthropic Claude with a hardcoded API key path. ApiSources-G1 introduces a configurable multi-provider system so agents can use different LLM backends. ApiSources-G3 evolves this to model-first selection: agents choose specific models (by model_id) from each ApiSource, with tier as a display-only tag.

## ApiSources-G2 APIs Documentation View
**Status:** implemented
**Tags:** stack:frontend
**Depends on:** ApiSources-G1

- [x] Top-level "APIs" tab in nav rail for browsing backend endpoint documentation
- [x] Lists all API routes grouped by module (project, chats, wiki, relay, config)
- [x] Displays method, path, handler name, and brief description per endpoint
- [x] Static content sourced from `specs/apis.ad`; editable via Specs workspace

## ApiSources-G3 Model-First Agent Configuration replaces Tier-based selection
**Status:** proposed
**Tags:** stack:both, module:api-sources
**Depends on:** ApiSources-G1

- [ ] AgentConfig stores `model_id` (reference to a specific model in an ApiSource) instead of `model_tier`
- [ ] Model tier becomes a tag/label on each ModelDefinition for display and reference only
- [ ] Frontend Agent config UI shows model list per ApiSource for direct model selection
- [ ] resolve_model() resolves directly by model_id, eliminating tier downgrade fallback logic
- [ ] Default AgentConfigs are updated to reference concrete model IDs instead of tier values
- [ ] Existing AgentConfig migrations gracefully convert tier-based configs to model-based

Currently agents select a model by choosing a tier (min/lite/mid/pro/max), which causes problems when an ApiSource doesn't have models for all tiers. The new design lets users directly select a specific model from the ApiSource's model list, with tier shown as a tag for reference. This ensures no agent is misconfigured due to missing tiers.
